<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-04-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-04-11"><hi rend="italic">April</hi>, 11, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your communication of the 9th instant, representing that
                            Rear-Admiral Theodoras Bailey and the prize commissioner at New York
                            have disregarded the arrangement in respect to the British mails on
                            board the captured steamer Peterhoff, and to inform you, in reply, that
                            the matter has been brought to the notice of the Secretary of the
                            Navy.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                            servant</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>